<h1>Refreshingly open</h1>
<p>Red Hat&reg; Enterprise Virtualization is built on 2 major open source projects: Kernel-based Virtual Machine (KVM) and oVirt. And Red Hat is an active member of the Open Virtualization Alliance (OVA).</p>
<p class="look"><a href="http://www.redhat.com/about/whyopensource/">Read more about Red Hat and open source</a></p>

<h2>KVM</h2>
<p>Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization Hypervisor, built directly from the KVM hypervisor, leverages the performance, scalability, and ecosystem of the Red Hat Enterprise Linux&reg; kernel for virtualization. So your VMs are powered by the same high-performance kernel that supports your most challenging Linux workloads. </p>

<p>KVM is a robust open source project supported by some of the leading vendors in the software industry, including:</p>
